com.mentorgen.tools.profile.instrument
クラス PerfMethodAdapter

java.lang.Object
  org.objectweb.asm.jip.MethodAdapter
      com.mentorgen.tools.profile.instrument.PerfMethodAdapter
すべての実装されたインタフェース:
MethodVisitor
public class PerfMethodAdapter
extends MethodAdapter

This class is responsible for instrumenting a method to call the profiler in order for performance data to be gathered. The basic idea is that the profiler is called when a method starts and when it exists which allows the profiler to gather performance data (note that a method can be exited from when an exception is thrown as well as when return is called). The one big caveate is static initializers. They are not called as part of the flow of the program — they are called by the classloader. Since they whole premise of the profiler is built on the idea of a orderly call stack, static initializers are not instrumented.

作成者:
Andrew Wilcox

インタフェース MethodVisitor の記述:

visitMethodInsn

public void visitMethodInsn(int opcode,
                            java.lang.String owner,
                            java.lang.String name,
                            java.lang.String desc)
インタフェース MethodVisitor の記述:
Visits a method instruction. A method instruction is an instruction that invokes a method.

定義:
インタフェース MethodVisitor 内の visitMethodInsn
オーバーライド:
クラス MethodAdapter 内の visitMethodInsn
パラメータ:
opcode - the opcode of the type instruction to be visited. This opcode is either INVOKEVIRTUAL, INVOKESPECIAL, INVOKESTATIC, INVOKEINTERFACE or INVOKEDYNAMIC.
owner - the internal name of the method's owner class (see getInternalName) or Opcodes.INVOKEDYNAMIC_OWNER.
name - the method's name.
desc - the method's descriptor (see Type).

                               Label handler,
                               java.lang.String type)
インタフェース MethodVisitor の記述:
Visits a try catch block.

定義:
インタフェース MethodVisitor 内の visitTryCatchBlock
オーバーライド:
クラス MethodAdapter 内の visitTryCatchBlock
パラメータ:
start - beginning of the exception handler's scope (inclusive).
end - end of the exception handler's scope (exclusive).
handler - beginning of the exception handler's code.
type - internal name of the type of exceptions handled by the handler, or null to catch any exceptions (for "finally" blocks).
